\subsection{Limitations and Future Extensions}

The present model is intentionally minimal to isolate the SOC network dynamics.
Important extensions for future work include:
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=1.5em]
  \item \textbf{Spatial embedding}: Placing the network on a 2-D or 3-D
        lattice to model tissue geometry and contact mechanics.
  \item \textbf{Immune response}: Adding a population of immune cells that
        preferentially target high-degree (hub) cancerous nodes, creating a
        competing cascade of clearance.
  \item \textbf{Drug pharmacokinetics}: Modelling drug action as a time-varying
        reduction in $\rho$ or increase in $\nu$, allowing optimal timing
        studies.
  \item \textbf{Metastasis}: Extending the model to a multi-tissue network to
        study when and how invasion crosses tissue boundaries.
  \item \textbf{Calibration to data}: Fitting $\alpha$, $\theta$, and $\rho$
        to clone-size distributions from patient tumour sequencing data.
\end{enumerate}

